[{"location":"api/#API","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Data-retrieval","page":"API","title":"Data retrieval","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"get_regional_data\nget_carbon_intensity\nget_todays_forecast","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#UKCarbonIntensityData.get_regional_data","page":"API","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData.get_regional_data","text":"get_carbon_intensity(start_date::ZonedDateTime, end_date::ZonedDateTime)\n\nReturns a NamedTuple with two fields named intensity and generation. Both tables contain data spanning the period defined by the start_date and end_date. the intensity field contains a dataframe of the forecast data of the regional carbon intensity, and the generation field contains a dataframe of the regional generation as a percent of the total generation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#UKCarbonIntensityData.get_carbon_intensity","page":"API","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData.get_carbon_intensity","text":"get_carbon_intensity(start_date::ZonedDateTime, end_date::ZonedDateTime)\n\nReturns a DataFrame of the nationwide forecast and actual carbon intensity between the given start_date and end_date.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#UKCarbonIntensityData.get_todays_forecast","page":"API","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData.get_todays_forecast","text":"get_todays_forecast(;regional::Bool=false, region::AbstractString=\"\")\n\nReturns a DataFrame of the forecast and actual carbon intensity between for the 48 hours of the day the query is called. By default return national level data, pass regional=true to return data with regional spatial resolution. To retreive data for a single region, pass the region = <desired region> where <desired region> must be included in the the AVAILABLE_REGIONS.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Plot-Recipes","page":"API","title":"Plot Recipes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"todays_plot\ncarbon_intensity","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#UKCarbonIntensityData.todays_plot","page":"API","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData.todays_plot","text":"todays_plot(; region = \"\")\n\nPlot the 48 forecast for the carbon intensity starting from midnight on the day that the function is called. By default shows the national forecast. If the region kwarg is a valid region, then plot data for this region only. Valid regions are contained in AVAILABLE_REGIONS.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#UKCarbonIntensityData.carbon_intensity","page":"API","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData.carbon_intensity","text":"carbon_intensity(start_date, end_date)\n\nPlots the recorded carbon intensity over the period given by the start_date and end_date.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Mappings","page":"API","title":"Mappings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"AVAILABLE_REGIONS","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#UKCarbonIntensityData.AVAILABLE_REGIONS","page":"API","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData.AVAILABLE_REGIONS","text":"Dict mapping region names to region ids.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = UKCarbonIntensityData","category":"page"},{"location":"#UKCarbonIntensityData","page":"Home","title":"UKCarbonIntensityData","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for UKCarbonIntensityData.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Retrieving-Data","page":"Home","title":"Retrieving Data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We can use this package to retrieve the recorded carbon intensity (measured in gCOâ‚‚/kWh) over a specified date range. ","category":"page"},{"location":"#National-data","page":"Home","title":"National data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using UKCarbonIntensityData\nusing Plots\nusing TimeZones\n\nstart_date = ZonedDateTime(2022, 01, 01, tz\"UTC\")\nend_date = ZonedDateTime(2022, 02, 28, tz\"UTC\")\n\n# get national level intensity data for the given period\nnational_data = get_carbon_intensity(start_date, end_date)\nfirst(national_data, 5)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Regional-data","page":"Home","title":"Regional data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We can also retrieve the forecasted carbon intensity at the regional level","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"regional_data = get_regional_data(start_date, end_date)\nregional_intensity = regional_data.intensity;\nregional_mix = regional_data.generation;\ndisplay(first(regional_mix))","category":"page"},{"location":"#Todays-forecast","page":"Home","title":"Todays forecast","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We can also grab the forecast data for the next 48 hours, at both national or regional levels.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"national_data = get_todays_forecast()\nfirst(national_data)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"regional_data = get_todays_forecast(regional = true)\nfirst(regional_data)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Plotting-Data","page":"Home","title":"Plotting Data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package also exports some recipes to plot the data. Below shows how we can retrieve the 48 hour forecast data, for the nation as a whole, ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"todays_plot()","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"or for a specific region","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"todays_plot(region = \"South Scotland\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"todays_plot(region = \"North West England\")","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We can also view the recorded carbon intensity over a given time period","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"carbon_intensity(start_date, end_date)","category":"page"}]
